00:20.488 --> 00:27.361
*

01:10.704 --> 01:13.341
- Or crying, or worse,
and you know, I mean,

01:13.374 --> 01:15.643
that's when I knew
I had to end things with her.

01:15.676 --> 01:17.711
You know?
So cut to five months later.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.213
I moved out, right?

01:19.247 --> 01:20.814
Same woman I broke up with

01:20.848 --> 01:22.883
shows up
at my door wearing heels

01:22.916 --> 01:24.718
and not much else, Dr. Jen.

01:24.752 --> 01:27.421
- And was this visit expected?

01:27.455 --> 01:28.489
- Hell, no.

01:28.522 --> 01:29.890
I mean, my new girlfriend,

01:29.923 --> 01:31.825
also an ex now,
opened the door.

01:31.859 --> 01:33.661
Yeah.

01:33.694 --> 01:35.663
She opened the door
to my admittedly hot,

01:35.696 --> 01:38.299
nearly nude ex-girlfriend.

01:38.332 --> 01:39.900
The thing is, Dr. Jen,

01:39.933 --> 01:42.270
I can't seem the find
the whole package.

01:42.303 --> 01:44.705
- I mean, being clear
on what you want

01:44.738 --> 01:46.140
is gonna help to figure out

01:46.174 --> 01:47.841
what is gonna fit into your life

01:47.875 --> 01:50.344
and what isn't.

01:50.378 --> 01:51.545
Look, let's try this.

01:51.579 --> 01:53.814
Why don't you tell me,

01:53.847 --> 01:56.417
what are the traits
of your perfect person?

01:56.450 --> 01:57.885
You know, what is she like?

01:57.918 --> 01:59.620
What does she look like?

01:59.653 --> 02:02.323
- Well, she's got to be smart,
educated,

02:02.356 --> 02:04.225
have a successful career
of her own.

02:04.258 --> 02:07.695
You know, actually, Dr. Jen,
now that I think of it,

02:07.728 --> 02:09.363
you are what I'm looking for.

02:09.396 --> 02:10.564
You're together.

02:10.598 --> 02:11.865
You're a relationship expert.

02:11.899 --> 02:13.467
You are the whole package.

02:13.501 --> 02:15.536
Hey, how about dinner sometime?

02:15.569 --> 02:19.540
- Kyle, I am--I'm so flattered,
and thank you so much.

02:19.573 --> 02:22.376
But I'm taken.

02:22.410 --> 02:26.514
I do wish you so much luck
in this quest,

02:26.547 --> 02:30.551
and remember, you create
the love that you deserve.

02:30.584 --> 02:34.555
Up next, we have
Lilith on line six.

02:34.588 --> 02:35.923
Hello, Lilith.

02:35.956 --> 02:37.958
- I'm here.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.628
- My screener said you had
a question about siblings.

02:40.661 --> 02:43.664
- That's right.
But why would I ask you?

02:43.697 --> 02:45.533
You think you're such an expert?

02:45.566 --> 02:48.569
A little birdie told me
your family's a total mess.

02:48.602 --> 02:51.772
Isn't that right?

02:51.805 --> 02:56.344
- You know, the family dynamic
is complex,

02:56.377 --> 02:58.879
mine included.

02:58.912 --> 03:01.949
It's how you handle these
situations that really matter.

03:01.982 --> 03:04.685
- Why don't you
talk about deadbeat dads

03:04.718 --> 03:07.321
or moms with endless streams
of boyfriends?

03:07.355 --> 03:09.890
Or how about commitment-phobic
career women?

03:09.923 --> 03:10.991
Huh?

03:11.024 --> 03:12.726
Huh?
[chuckles]

03:12.760 --> 03:14.395
- You sound
really angry, Lilith.

03:14.428 --> 03:15.896
- You think you're some expert.

03:15.929 --> 03:17.631
Well, you're no expert.
You're just a fake.

03:17.665 --> 03:19.833
You're a fake! Fake--

03:19.867 --> 03:21.235
[switch clicks,
audio cuts off abruptly]

03:21.269 --> 03:22.603
- This is the Dr. Jen show,

03:22.636 --> 03:24.805
and we'll be back
right after this.

03:27.308 --> 03:28.242
- [grunts]

03:38.652 --> 03:41.455
- It's for my mom, Georgina.
- Aww.

03:41.489 --> 03:43.357
- So is it true you're
working on another book?

03:43.391 --> 03:44.725
- Yes.
It comes out this Christmas.

03:44.758 --> 03:46.660
- Is there anything you could
tell us about it?

03:46.694 --> 03:48.329
- I can't say too much quite
yet, but if you keep listening,

03:48.362 --> 03:49.563
I promise there'll be
some sneak-peeks.

03:49.597 --> 03:50.564
- Oh, we will.
- Thank you.

03:50.598 --> 03:52.400
Nice to meet you guys.

03:52.433 --> 03:53.501
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you. Thank you.

03:53.534 --> 03:54.835
- Thanks, Dr. Jen.
- Hey, look.

03:54.868 --> 03:56.704
- It's so good.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.038
- You're a liar.
- Oh, my--

03:58.071 --> 03:59.940
- You're a fake.
- Hey, hey, hey, hey,

03:59.973 --> 04:01.542
hey, whoa, whoa whoa--what
do you think you're doing?

04:01.575 --> 04:02.910
- I hate--let me go.
Let me go.

04:02.943 --> 04:04.345
- What do you think
you're doing?

04:04.378 --> 04:05.679
- You're a fake.
You're a fake.

04:05.713 --> 04:07.381
You're a fake!
I hate you! Let me go.

04:07.415 --> 04:08.649
- Hey, chill, chill, chill,
chill, chill.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.651
- I hate you.
I hate you.

04:10.684 --> 04:13.454
[indistinct police radio
chatter]

04:16.524 --> 04:18.992
- All right, we're taking her in
to process and arrest.

04:19.026 --> 04:21.495
- No, no, no. But why does
she have to be arrested?

04:21.529 --> 04:22.730
- It was an assault.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.598
Witnesses--
- Right.

04:24.632 --> 04:26.634
But I'm not pressing
criminal charges.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.702
- Jen, why not? She's dangerous.
She might hurt somebody else.

04:28.736 --> 04:30.971
- She assaulted you.
- She needs mental care,

04:31.004 --> 04:32.906
not to be caged up
like an animal.

04:32.940 --> 04:36.444
- You got no say over me,
bitch.

04:36.477 --> 04:39.046
- She seems like
a total nut job, Jen.

04:39.079 --> 04:41.549
- [sighs]

04:41.582 --> 04:43.651
She's my sister, Gail.

04:45.653 --> 04:47.655
- Wait.
That's Cassie?

04:51.425 --> 04:55.095
- She needs psychiatric care.

04:55.128 --> 04:57.097
- It's your call, doctor.
- You can't do this to me.

04:57.130 --> 04:58.866
What about my girls?

04:58.899 --> 05:01.669
What's gonna happen to my girls?

05:01.702 --> 05:04.572
- I'll make arrangements with
social services, get my nieces.

05:04.605 --> 05:06.039
They can stay with me.

05:06.073 --> 05:07.875
I'm next of kin.

05:07.908 --> 05:08.976
Thank you so much
for everything.

05:09.009 --> 05:10.478
- Absolutely.
- Thank you.

05:20.020 --> 05:22.956
[mysterious music]

05:22.990 --> 05:29.863
*

06:01.529 --> 06:03.163
- Ah, hello.
Dr. Burgess,

06:03.196 --> 06:04.998
I'm Robin Aldriss
from social services.

06:05.032 --> 06:06.867
I've been assigned
to the Murphy girls' case.

06:06.900 --> 06:08.636
- Great.

06:08.669 --> 06:10.904
- Listen.
I need to warn you.

06:10.938 --> 06:12.139
It's pretty bad in there.

06:20.514 --> 06:22.049
Quite the decorating job,

06:22.082 --> 06:24.151
considering they've only
been here four months.

06:24.184 --> 06:26.119
It's no wonder
you can never find them.

06:26.153 --> 06:28.856
They haven't been
in any place long enough.

06:28.889 --> 06:29.890
- [sighs]

06:39.232 --> 06:40.601
Hi.

06:47.475 --> 06:49.710
Quinn, Olivia...

06:49.743 --> 06:53.514
it's been so long.

06:53.547 --> 06:57.050
You're both so grown up,
I can't even tell you apart.

06:57.084 --> 07:00.888
- You can't tell us apart.

07:00.921 --> 07:03.657
- [sighs]
I'm Olivia, and Quinn's right.

07:03.691 --> 07:05.626
Even Mom can't tell us apart.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.595
- Girls, I need you
to pack your things.

07:07.628 --> 07:10.130
It's best we get
to your aunt's house soon.

07:10.163 --> 07:12.966
- How long do we have
to be with her?

07:13.000 --> 07:16.103
- You know, your mother is
with the best doctors.

07:16.136 --> 07:18.939
She's getting the best care
that there is.

07:18.972 --> 07:21.675
You just have to stay with me
until she's better.

07:21.709 --> 07:23.777
In the meantime, we get to spend
some time together

07:23.811 --> 07:25.513
and get to know
each other again.

07:28.949 --> 07:30.150
I missed you both so much.

07:32.886 --> 07:34.522
- Ome-cay on-way.

07:45.899 --> 07:49.169
- Well, the nice news is that
you guys have summer break.

07:49.202 --> 07:51.639
You know, we get
a nice long visit.

07:51.672 --> 07:53.674
Plus, I have a pool.
Do you guys like to swim?

07:53.707 --> 07:55.709
- Why can't we just
stay at our house?

07:55.743 --> 07:58.712
I mean, we're old enough
to take care of ourselves.

07:58.746 --> 08:01.114
- I'm sorry.
So you're Quinn, right?

08:03.083 --> 08:04.652
Okay. look.

08:04.685 --> 08:06.286
I know that this is all new,

08:06.319 --> 08:12.159
and this is sort of
a difficult time,

08:12.192 --> 08:13.961
but I think it's gonna
be really important

08:13.994 --> 08:16.163
to just stay busy at the house.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.866
You know, I have a pool.
You guys can swim.

08:18.899 --> 08:20.634
I even bought you guys
some new bikes.

08:20.668 --> 08:22.035
- Oh, bikes.

08:22.069 --> 08:23.937
That's great.
That'll fix everything.

08:33.179 --> 08:36.116
- Wow, you live around here?

08:36.149 --> 08:38.952
- I think you guys might learn
to really like it around here.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.064
Come on in.

09:42.049 --> 09:46.186
- This place looks like
some movie.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.188
- You must
be loaded.

09:48.221 --> 09:50.658
Mom said you were rich,
but not this rich.

09:50.691 --> 09:52.626
- Well, uh,

09:52.660 --> 09:55.228
I guess all the hard work
has paid off.

09:55.262 --> 09:58.031
Come on.
Let's go see your rooms.

09:58.065 --> 09:59.266
They're upstairs.

10:01.001 --> 10:02.369
Do you need help with your bag?

10:02.402 --> 10:03.771
- Mm-mm.

10:13.046 --> 10:14.982
- They're just down the hall.

10:20.788 --> 10:23.056
So the room's
just right here.

10:27.427 --> 10:28.962
So?

10:33.901 --> 10:36.670
I put up a couple things,
but I had no idea

10:36.704 --> 10:38.371
what a teenage girl
would put on her wall.

10:38.405 --> 10:42.676
So you guys feel free
to put up whatever you'd like.

10:42.710 --> 10:45.012
- There's only one bed?

10:45.045 --> 10:48.716
- That's because you guys
get your own rooms.

10:48.749 --> 10:50.417
- But we've always
shared a room.

10:50.450 --> 10:52.319
- I'm sorry.

10:52.352 --> 10:53.954
You're gonna have to help me
with this for a while.

10:53.987 --> 10:55.055
You're--

10:55.088 --> 10:57.157
- All Quinn wants to know

10:57.190 --> 11:00.994
is why you keep trying
to split up our family.

11:01.028 --> 11:04.364
- You know, Olivia, why don't
we go, check out your room?

11:04.397 --> 11:06.333
Give it a try.

11:06.366 --> 11:08.936
You might find that you
like your own space.

11:08.969 --> 11:10.337
Okay?

11:32.793 --> 11:35.362
You know, if you guys promise
to share it, you can keep it.

11:35.395 --> 11:37.164
- We had one.

11:37.197 --> 11:40.333
Mom pawned our microwave
to get it.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.401
It broke.

11:43.436 --> 11:46.907
- Well, this one's yours.

11:46.940 --> 11:48.441
- We're kind of starved.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.310
How about some of those chips?

11:50.343 --> 11:52.312
- Of course.

11:52.345 --> 11:54.247
I just--I keep them up there
because they are so addicting.

11:54.281 --> 11:56.183
So I like to keep them
out of reach.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.851
- We noticed.

11:57.885 --> 11:59.987
- So what are you
discovering on there?

12:00.020 --> 12:00.854
Anything cool?

12:11.231 --> 12:13.266
[metallic click]

12:13.300 --> 12:15.836
- [gasps]

12:15.869 --> 12:17.838
- Well, that was exciting.

12:24.511 --> 12:27.280
- Looks like this
little guy fell off.

12:27.314 --> 12:29.349
- Hmm.

12:29.382 --> 12:31.118
That's weird.
It's new.

12:39.259 --> 12:42.195
[plaintive music]

12:42.229 --> 12:49.102
*

12:55.142 --> 12:58.078
That is from when
your mom and I

12:58.111 --> 13:01.548
went to horse camp
when we were younger.

13:01.581 --> 13:03.984
That was the first time
that we were away from our mom.

13:06.486 --> 13:10.157
It was the first time we really
felt like we had broken through.

13:10.190 --> 13:12.159
- Broken through what?

13:12.192 --> 13:14.027
- You know,

13:14.061 --> 13:18.465
our mom was really hard
on your mom

13:18.498 --> 13:20.333
when we were growing up,

13:20.367 --> 13:23.570
and she had a lot of resentment

13:23.603 --> 13:26.373
towards me because of it.

13:31.144 --> 13:34.114
[upbeat music]

13:34.147 --> 13:41.021
*

13:47.895 --> 13:50.530
[indistinct chatter]

14:14.187 --> 14:16.189
- Quinn, Olivia?

14:17.991 --> 14:21.594
What are you guys doing in here?

14:21.628 --> 14:23.997
- We couldn't sleep.

14:24.031 --> 14:26.633
- You've been in here all night?

14:26.666 --> 14:29.236
- Yeah.
So?

14:29.269 --> 14:31.204
I like it.
Olivia likes it.

14:31.238 --> 14:33.006
So what's the problem?

14:33.040 --> 14:34.574
- [sighs]

14:37.210 --> 14:38.411
Well...

14:45.452 --> 14:48.021
It is kind of a cool
little spot.

14:48.055 --> 14:51.224
It's a little cramped,
but it's cozy.

14:52.659 --> 14:55.228
Is that what you
like about it?

14:55.262 --> 14:58.298
- Not really.

14:58.331 --> 15:01.068
- You worried about your mom?

15:01.101 --> 15:03.203
- It's okay, Olivia.

15:03.236 --> 15:05.072
You can stop.

15:05.105 --> 15:07.140
She's just messing
with you, Jen.

15:07.174 --> 15:08.275
I'm Quinn.

15:12.745 --> 15:16.950
If you really need to know,
we come to places like this

15:16.984 --> 15:20.253
when we need to shut people
like you out.

15:20.287 --> 15:23.190
When everybody's
prying into our minds,

15:23.223 --> 15:25.725
we'll do anything
to make you go away.

15:25.758 --> 15:28.261
- I love you guys.

15:28.295 --> 15:31.264
When you love someone, you will
do anything to help them.

15:33.266 --> 15:37.370
- Nice try,
but that's psycho talk.

15:37.404 --> 15:40.007
- I can't imagine
how it must feel

15:40.040 --> 15:41.374
to suddenly feel like someone

15:41.408 --> 15:42.742
who you thought
didn't care about you

15:42.775 --> 15:46.146
for so long finally cares.

15:46.179 --> 15:48.248
You must wonder where I've been
all these years.

15:48.281 --> 15:51.451
- Maybe we didn't need you
in our life.

15:51.484 --> 15:55.255
Maybe our mom got away
from you on purpose.

15:55.288 --> 15:58.591
- All that stuff
is in the past,

15:58.625 --> 16:01.995
and I know I want you guys
to give this a chance

16:02.029 --> 16:05.532
and give us a chance,

16:05.565 --> 16:09.669
because I know
that I really want to.

16:19.779 --> 16:22.115
- How long have you
been a teacher?

16:22.149 --> 16:23.250
- Hmm.

16:23.283 --> 16:24.717
[laughs]
It's--

16:24.751 --> 16:27.454
Gosh, it's almost
been ten years.

16:27.487 --> 16:28.688
It seems like yesterday,
though.

16:28.721 --> 16:30.323
- He's really good too.

16:30.357 --> 16:32.159
Kevin's classes
always fill up.

16:32.192 --> 16:35.062
- So what grades
do you teach?

16:35.095 --> 16:37.064
- I teach science
to mostly seniors

16:37.097 --> 16:39.732
at a small
private school.

16:39.766 --> 16:42.435
- So how come you guys
aren't married?

16:42.469 --> 16:44.137
- Yeah.

16:44.171 --> 16:46.206
You afraid Jen's whacked,
like our mom?

16:46.239 --> 16:48.775
- Girls--
- It's okay.

16:48.808 --> 16:51.511
I'd be happy to answer that.

16:51.544 --> 16:56.183
Your aunt is the most
amazing woman I've ever known.

16:56.216 --> 16:58.818
And someday,
if I'm lucky,

16:58.851 --> 17:01.588
she will marry me.

17:01.621 --> 17:05.392
Now, what I want to kn is how
are you girls liking it here?

17:07.460 --> 17:10.363
- We'd feel better
if we could see our mom.

17:10.396 --> 17:12.365
- Well, I have some news.

17:12.398 --> 17:13.665
We're actually
scheduled

17:13.700 --> 17:15.734
for a visit
with your mom tomorrow.

17:15.768 --> 17:18.738
- Tomorrow?

17:18.771 --> 17:21.374
- But I need to explain
a little something to you first.

17:21.407 --> 17:23.843
I think she is planning on
being there a little bit longer

17:23.876 --> 17:26.779
than we all
originally thought.

17:26.813 --> 17:28.848
- Like, for how long?

17:28.881 --> 17:31.518
- Well, her doctor
has suggested

17:31.551 --> 17:33.820
long-term treatment.

17:33.853 --> 17:36.489
It's about three months.

17:36.523 --> 17:38.591
- So she's gonna be alone
in some creepy place

17:38.625 --> 17:40.493
for three months?

17:40.527 --> 17:43.296
- I know that it's longer
than we all thought,

17:43.330 --> 17:44.797
but she's agreed to this,

17:44.831 --> 17:46.633
and she's actually
told her doctors

17:46.666 --> 17:48.601
that she's happy about this.

17:48.635 --> 17:50.403
This is a really
good sign.

17:50.437 --> 17:52.605
- She wouldn't.

17:52.639 --> 17:55.242
- Look, I know this is
really hard to hear,

17:55.275 --> 17:56.309
but your mom needs
all the support--

17:56.343 --> 17:58.178
[glass shatters]

17:58.211 --> 17:59.446
- Quinn.

18:11.324 --> 18:13.760
- A little wine,
a little relaxation time--

18:13.793 --> 18:16.129
- Yes.
- It's gonna be okay.

18:26.206 --> 18:27.407
[glass crunching]

18:27.440 --> 18:29.276
- Ow, oh--

18:29.309 --> 18:30.910
- What?

18:30.943 --> 18:34.214
- It's glass.

18:34.247 --> 18:35.782
Oh, my God,
there's glass in my hand.

18:35.815 --> 18:38.385
- Oh, my God.
- Mm!

18:38.418 --> 18:40.453
- Come on.
Let's clean that up.

18:40.487 --> 18:42.155
- Oh, my God.

18:42.189 --> 18:44.924
[suspenseful music]

18:44.957 --> 18:51.798
*

18:58.471 --> 19:00.173
- You sure it doesn't hurt?

19:00.207 --> 19:01.774
- Yeah. It's fine.

19:01.808 --> 19:02.909
- Are you lying to me?

19:02.942 --> 19:04.777
- Yes. It hurts.

19:08.748 --> 19:09.782
- What happened?

19:12.452 --> 19:14.221
- Did we wake you guys up?

19:14.254 --> 19:15.922
- What's going on?

19:15.955 --> 19:19.392
- Oh, there was some glass
on the seat cushion outside.

19:19.426 --> 19:21.261
I cut my hand.

19:21.294 --> 19:22.662
It's nothing to worry about.

19:22.695 --> 19:25.198
- It was probably
from Quinn's glass.

19:25.232 --> 19:26.533
- How was I supposed to know?

19:26.566 --> 19:28.668
It's not like
I d it on purpose.

19:28.701 --> 19:29.902
- Okay.

19:29.936 --> 19:32.605
- I should probably
head home.

19:32.639 --> 19:33.640
- Yeah.

19:36.809 --> 19:37.810
- Good night, girls.

19:43.483 --> 19:44.817
- Okay, look.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.219
There's no sense
in blaming each other

19:46.253 --> 19:47.220
for something like this.

19:47.254 --> 19:48.588
This is an accident.

19:48.621 --> 19:49.456
- Good night.

19:53.426 --> 19:54.527
- Good night.

19:58.265 --> 20:00.800
I'm gonna go to bed,
and I think you should too.

20:00.833 --> 20:02.602
We have a big day tomorrow,

20:02.635 --> 20:04.704
and we've had enough excitement
for one night.

20:04.737 --> 20:06.839
Besides, you get
to see your mom.

20:06.873 --> 20:09.242
- Okay.
Good night, Jen.

20:09.276 --> 20:09.909
- Good night.

20:22.822 --> 20:25.625
[indistinct chatter]

20:51.784 --> 20:52.752
Thank you.

20:52.785 --> 20:53.620
- Here you go.

21:39.366 --> 21:41.368
- Ah, we finally
meet in person.

21:41.401 --> 21:42.702
I've listened
to your show for years.

21:42.735 --> 21:44.404
- Oh.

21:44.437 --> 21:45.572
- I see you got
the record you requested?

21:45.605 --> 21:47.073
- Yes, I do.
Thank you.

21:47.106 --> 21:48.841
- Hey, Doc!

21:48.875 --> 21:50.076
If she's such an expert,

21:50.109 --> 21:53.980
why am I here?

21:54.013 --> 21:55.382
Oh, I know.

21:55.415 --> 21:56.616
It's your fault I'm here.

21:56.649 --> 21:57.984
- Cassie.

21:58.017 --> 21:58.918
- You think you can
take my babies?

21:58.951 --> 22:00.520
- Nurse.

22:00.553 --> 22:01.588
- You think you can take
what's mine?

22:01.621 --> 22:02.922
They're my babies.

22:02.955 --> 22:04.557
- No. Come on.
- They're my babies.

22:04.591 --> 22:06.058
They're mine!

22:06.092 --> 22:07.727
- Okay. Relax.
- Don't escalate, Cassie.

22:07.760 --> 22:09.128
Keeping calm is important.
- My babies--let me go.

22:09.161 --> 22:11.398
They're my babies.
Girls--they're mine.

22:11.431 --> 22:13.433
- No one is taking your girls.
- They're mine. They're mine!

22:13.466 --> 22:14.534
- It's okay.
- Okay. Fine.

23:36.248 --> 23:39.051
- Okay.
What'd I miss?

23:39.085 --> 23:40.453
- The kid's
freaking out again.

23:40.487 --> 23:42.755
- He is?
- He's crazy!

23:42.789 --> 23:44.123
He's going too fast!

23:44.156 --> 23:45.992
[indistinct shouting on TV]
- [laughs]

23:46.025 --> 23:48.995
[engine revving, wheels squeal]

23:49.028 --> 23:50.530
Come on, get him!
Get him!

23:50.563 --> 23:51.764
He's just--he's over there.

23:51.798 --> 23:54.834
What are you doing?

23:54.867 --> 23:56.903
Go!

23:56.936 --> 23:59.238
[indistinct chatter on TV]

23:59.271 --> 24:00.640
- [gasps, moans]

24:05.011 --> 24:07.046
I have to go
rinse this off.

24:07.079 --> 24:09.215
Oh, I don't know
what's happening.

24:09.248 --> 24:12.151
[suspenseful music]

24:12.184 --> 24:19.025
*

24:19.058 --> 24:20.560
- How's your breathing?

24:20.593 --> 24:22.995
- It's fine, but my skin
is on fire.

24:23.029 --> 24:24.864
- Well, have you noticed any
difference in your breathing?

24:24.897 --> 24:27.567
I have your EpiPen right here.

24:27.600 --> 24:29.769
- Babe, no. It's, like,
a reaction to that cream.

24:31.170 --> 24:32.939
It hurts so bad.

24:32.972 --> 24:34.807
- Cold, cold, cold water--
cold water.

24:34.841 --> 24:36.108
That's it.

24:38.978 --> 24:41.013
You can do it.
Keep your arm in there.

24:41.047 --> 24:43.616
It's okay.
Hold still.

24:43.650 --> 24:46.586
Let the water cool the burn.

24:46.619 --> 24:49.155
- Ow.
[moans]

24:49.188 --> 24:50.957
- There you go.

24:50.990 --> 24:52.692
Give it some time.

25:22.288 --> 25:25.124
[phone buzzing]

25:33.766 --> 25:35.902
- Hey, Gail.
It's Jen. Listen.

25:35.935 --> 25:37.804
I hate to do this last-minute,

25:37.837 --> 25:40.907
but I just--I can't host
the show this week.

25:40.940 --> 25:43.275
I just got--truthfully,
it's the girls.

25:43.309 --> 25:45.912
They just--they need
more attention right now.

25:45.945 --> 25:48.815
They're really having
a hard time, and it's hard.

25:48.848 --> 25:51.117
Okay? Just run a show
from last year.

25:51.150 --> 25:52.952
Cole knows which ones
that I liked.

25:52.985 --> 25:55.354
Oh, and can you call Dr. Frank

25:55.387 --> 25:57.857
and ask if he can make
a house call today?

25:57.890 --> 26:00.326
I got a weird reaction
I want him to take a look at.

26:00.359 --> 26:02.161
All right, and Gail, thank you.

26:02.194 --> 26:04.296
I don't know
what I would do without you.

26:04.330 --> 26:06.866
Bye.

26:14.106 --> 26:15.842
Dr. Frank, thank you so much

26:15.875 --> 26:17.109
for coming out
on such short notice.

26:17.143 --> 26:18.678
- Of course.
No problem.

26:18.711 --> 26:20.980
Now, you wanted me
to look at your arm.

26:21.013 --> 26:22.381
- I know I had
a bad allergic reaction

26:22.414 --> 26:24.717
to a new moisturizer.

26:24.751 --> 26:26.753
- Yes.
Well--

26:26.786 --> 26:28.220
[chuckles]

26:28.254 --> 26:33.092
Oh, that is not
an allergic reaction, Jen.

26:33.125 --> 26:34.360
That's a burn.

26:34.393 --> 26:36.228
It's a chemical burn.

26:36.262 --> 26:37.864
It's bad too.

26:37.897 --> 26:39.799
That could've caused
severe nerve damage.

26:39.832 --> 26:41.133
- Well, needless to say,

26:41.167 --> 26:45.004
I am not gonna use
that moisturizer anymore.

26:45.037 --> 26:46.773
- Make sure to keep your arm
away from any heat,

26:46.806 --> 26:48.340
and it'll be fine.

26:48.374 --> 26:49.809
- Thank you so much
for coming out again.

26:49.842 --> 26:51.243
- Any time.
- I really appreciate it.

26:51.277 --> 26:52.144
- Don't worry.
- Okay.

28:12.759 --> 28:14.126
- What you doing?
- [gasps]

28:14.160 --> 28:15.895
Don't do that.

28:15.928 --> 28:18.130
- Whoa.
What got into you?

28:18.164 --> 28:20.199
- Nothing.

28:20.232 --> 28:21.768
- Okay.
You're totally lying.

28:21.801 --> 28:22.701
What's going on?

28:26.205 --> 28:28.240
- It's my arm.

28:28.274 --> 28:30.910
Dr. Frank was right.
It's a chemical burn.

28:30.943 --> 28:32.044
- You know that for sure?

28:34.046 --> 28:35.815
- I tested it.

28:35.848 --> 28:38.417
It has pool acid in it.

28:38.450 --> 28:40.186
- Oh, my God.
- Mm-hmm.

28:40.219 --> 28:44.323
- Jen,
this is getting nuts.

28:44.356 --> 28:46.392
You could be
in real danger.

28:46.425 --> 28:48.294
You have to do something
about the girls.

28:48.327 --> 28:49.929
I mean, there's two of them,
and together, they could--

28:49.962 --> 28:51.463
- No, they're not gonna
do anything serious.

28:51.497 --> 28:53.365
They're just--

28:53.399 --> 28:55.434
They're acting out the anger
of their mother on me.

28:55.467 --> 28:57.236
- I used to act out
when I was a kid too,

28:57.269 --> 29:00.006
but it didn't involve
giving people chemical burns.

29:00.039 --> 29:02.541
What are you gonna do?

29:02.574 --> 29:05.277
- I don't know.

29:05.311 --> 29:07.246
I've also noticed
that there've been

29:07.279 --> 29:09.849
a couple things missing
around the house--

29:09.882 --> 29:11.383
some valuable things.

29:11.417 --> 29:13.319
- Well, this just keeps
getting better, doesn't it?

29:13.352 --> 29:16.856
- Mm-hmm.
And I can't accuse them.

29:16.889 --> 29:18.891
Not right now.

29:18.925 --> 29:20.326
I need them to trust me.

29:20.359 --> 29:22.061
- Well, I want them
to trust you too, Jen,

29:22.094 --> 29:23.195
but I also don't want them
running around,

29:23.229 --> 29:25.898
setting up traps for us
in the house.

29:25.932 --> 29:27.800
What if you get
some of those nanny cams?

29:27.834 --> 29:28.868
- Gail--
- Yeah.

29:28.901 --> 29:30.336
You know, the little ones.

29:30.369 --> 29:32.238
You could just hide them
in a corner, and that way,

29:32.271 --> 29:33.906
you could see what's going on
without asking them.

29:33.940 --> 29:36.308
Look. Jen, I know
that you want to trust them.

29:36.342 --> 29:38.945
But this is starting
to get scary.

29:38.978 --> 29:40.512
I mean, they've never
had a role model.

29:40.546 --> 29:43.883
We have no idea
what they're gonna do.

29:43.916 --> 29:46.853
- I knew this was
gonna be difficult.

29:46.886 --> 29:48.454
It's just gonna
take some time.

29:48.487 --> 29:50.522
- I still think that it
would be good for everyone

29:50.556 --> 29:54.927
if you knew a little bit more
about what they were up to,

29:54.961 --> 29:57.063
you know,
for their own sakes.

29:57.096 --> 29:57.964
- Yeah.

30:01.267 --> 30:03.102
- Get the nanny cams.

30:20.652 --> 30:23.555
[suspenseful music]

30:23.589 --> 30:30.462
*

31:24.050 --> 31:26.618
- Olivia, can we talk
for a second?

31:26.652 --> 31:28.087
Would you mind?

31:28.120 --> 31:30.589
- Sure.
Just me?

31:30.622 --> 31:33.292
- Do you mind?

31:33.325 --> 31:34.526
- Sure.

31:44.370 --> 31:47.439
- So what's up?

31:47.473 --> 31:50.409
- Well, one thing that

31:50.442 --> 31:54.480
I have always
admired about you,

31:54.513 --> 31:58.550
good or bad,
is that you speak your mind,

31:58.584 --> 32:03.022
and Quinn is not
always like that.

32:03.055 --> 32:06.993
You know, she holds
in her feelings,

32:07.026 --> 32:09.628
and I'm a little concerned.

32:09.661 --> 32:11.663
- What do you want me
to do about it?

32:11.697 --> 32:13.532
- Well, I was hoping you could
give me some ideas

32:13.565 --> 32:16.168
on how to talk to her.

32:16.202 --> 32:17.369
- That's it?

32:17.403 --> 32:19.438
- That's a lot.

32:19.471 --> 32:22.441
It's not easy to
share your feelings

32:22.474 --> 32:25.177
when you're not used
to being that way.

32:25.211 --> 32:26.478
You know, you guys are twins,

32:26.512 --> 32:29.348
but you're
very different people.

32:29.381 --> 32:31.483
- You're way off.

32:31.517 --> 32:33.685
Quinn agrees with me
on everything.

32:33.719 --> 32:38.057
If I say something,
she's already thinking it.

32:38.090 --> 32:39.625
We're just unhappy
that our mom's locked up

32:39.658 --> 32:42.594
and she's away from us.

32:42.628 --> 32:47.566
- I need you guys to trust
that this is the right thing.

32:47.599 --> 32:51.037
Maybe you can help Quinn
to understand that too,

32:51.070 --> 32:53.539
that I just want
what's best for your mom.

32:53.572 --> 32:55.174
We all do.

32:55.207 --> 32:57.276
Everyone is just
trying to do what's right.

33:07.753 --> 33:11.157
- Hello. It's me.
Morning!

33:11.190 --> 33:13.659
- Morning, Gail.

33:13.692 --> 33:16.628
- Hello.

33:16.662 --> 33:18.197
- There's coffee.

33:18.230 --> 33:20.199
- Oh, coffee.
I so need it today.

33:20.232 --> 33:23.269
It smells amazing.

33:23.302 --> 33:25.537
You make the best, Jen.

33:35.181 --> 33:36.615
Hey, I have an idea.

33:36.648 --> 33:38.650
What do you think
about a day off?

33:38.684 --> 33:40.452
I have a feeling
we could use a beach day.

33:40.486 --> 33:43.622
- Oh, um...I--

33:43.655 --> 33:45.424
Yeah, I think
that's a great idea.

33:45.457 --> 33:48.094
- Yeah?
What do you guys think?

33:48.127 --> 33:49.161
Beach day?

34:04.643 --> 34:06.578
- All right.
So 20 minutes, I'll be back.

34:06.612 --> 34:09.281
Is that okay?
Girls, is that all right?

34:09.315 --> 34:11.449
- We'll hold down the fort.
Have a good run.

34:19.658 --> 34:22.293
- This feels awesome.

34:22.328 --> 34:25.364
- So do you and Jen
come here often?

34:25.397 --> 34:26.565
- Not enough.

34:26.598 --> 34:28.400
- You get in.

34:34.773 --> 34:36.475
- You guys just discovered

34:36.507 --> 34:39.445
my number one favorite thing
to do at the beach.

34:39.478 --> 34:41.447
- You get in.
You get in.

34:41.480 --> 34:42.547
- Okay.

34:50.688 --> 34:52.358
[sighs]

34:52.391 --> 34:54.293
I like to bury myself

34:54.326 --> 34:56.895
like a warm, squishy cocoon.

34:56.928 --> 35:00.132
- Jen! Jen, come look!

35:00.166 --> 35:01.233
- Oh, hon,
she can't hear you.

35:01.267 --> 35:02.668
She's way too far.

35:30.562 --> 35:32.231
- Thanks.

35:32.264 --> 35:33.699
- Sure.

35:33.732 --> 35:36.502
- Quinn, you're going
to hold us up.

35:36.535 --> 35:39.171
Mom's waiting.

35:39.205 --> 35:40.206
- It's okay.
I'll finish.

35:40.239 --> 35:41.440
- Okay.

35:43.909 --> 35:45.577
- Why FaceTime?

35:45.611 --> 35:47.813
Why can't we go
and see her like last time?

35:47.846 --> 35:50.416
- Well, you know,

35:50.449 --> 35:53.252
the last visit was
really hard on your mom.

35:53.285 --> 35:56.522
The nurse thought
that this was better.

35:56.555 --> 35:59.825
I mean, this is a good step.

35:59.858 --> 36:01.193
Come on.
Let's check.

36:01.227 --> 36:02.228
Let's see if she's on there.

36:06.865 --> 36:08.200
- Hi, guys.

36:08.234 --> 36:10.469
Can you see me okay?
- Yes.

36:10.502 --> 36:12.204
- I'll be monitoring your visit.

36:12.238 --> 36:14.606
It just means I can hear you.

36:14.640 --> 36:15.907
If the call
becomes unmanageable,

36:15.941 --> 36:18.310
I'll end it immediately.
Okay?

36:18.344 --> 36:20.312
both: Okay.

36:20.346 --> 36:22.748
- You can stop the call anytime
by pushing the eject button

36:22.781 --> 36:24.616
at the top right of your screen.

36:24.650 --> 36:25.951
You got that?

36:31.623 --> 36:34.560
- Oh, God.
I miss my girls.

36:34.593 --> 36:35.627
[laughs]

36:35.661 --> 36:36.795
Olivia...

36:36.828 --> 36:39.431
- Hi, Mom.
I miss you.

36:39.465 --> 36:41.633
- And my Quinn.

36:41.667 --> 36:43.001
- Hi, Mom.

36:43.034 --> 36:45.571
- [laughs]
I missed my girls.

36:45.604 --> 36:47.773
So have you girls
been being good

36:47.806 --> 36:51.643
and being very careful
with your aunt's nice things?

36:51.677 --> 36:53.479
- Yeah. Yeah.

36:53.512 --> 36:55.581
We've totally been
good and careful and all that.

36:55.614 --> 36:57.449
- [laughs]
I knew you would be.

36:57.483 --> 36:59.851
Oh, I miss you so much,

36:59.885 --> 37:05.424
and I'm so glad you both get
to stay in her beautiful house.

37:05.457 --> 37:06.592
You're very lucky girls.

37:06.625 --> 37:09.027
- Yeah, yeah.
It's huge.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.530
And Jen gave us, like,
our own separate bedrooms,

37:11.563 --> 37:15.734
and we each get our own tub
and shower and closet.

37:15.767 --> 37:17.636
- I wish you were here, Mom.

37:17.669 --> 37:19.405
- Yeah.

37:19.438 --> 37:20.506
- Mom?

37:20.539 --> 37:21.540
- What's wrong, honey?

37:21.573 --> 37:23.609
You sound so sad.

37:23.642 --> 37:24.810
- We just want you back.

37:24.843 --> 37:27.379
We want
our old lives back.

37:27.413 --> 37:29.848
Do you really need to be there
for three months?

37:29.881 --> 37:31.617
- I do.

37:31.650 --> 37:34.286
I really do, sweetie.

37:34.320 --> 37:36.788
Being here longer
is a good thing.

37:36.822 --> 37:40.559
The best thing you two can do
is be patient.

37:48.834 --> 37:51.437
Good things come
to those who wait.

37:53.439 --> 37:54.640
[laughs]

37:54.673 --> 37:55.507
I love you.

38:04.082 --> 38:06.918
[mysterious music]

38:06.952 --> 38:13.825
*

38:43.389 --> 38:44.723
- Hey, Sissy,

38:44.756 --> 38:46.057
should we take this?

39:53.925 --> 39:56.127
"My commitment to Kevin
seems less important

39:56.161 --> 39:58.029
than helping the girls."

39:58.063 --> 40:00.532
So dramatic.

40:00.566 --> 40:02.067
The shrink needs a shrink.

40:23.054 --> 40:24.590
- I think I found it.

40:33.599 --> 40:35.901
Take a picture.

40:49.815 --> 40:54.019
- Remember, you create
the love that you deserve.

40:54.052 --> 40:55.754
- Mom's not in it.

40:55.787 --> 40:57.756
Neither are we.

40:57.789 --> 40:59.491
Everything goes to
some stupid charity.

40:59.525 --> 41:03.962
That's how much she cares
about us, Quinn.

41:03.995 --> 41:05.664
- That's all the time
we have today.

41:05.697 --> 41:07.699
I'm Dr. Jen,
and thank you for listening.

41:11.236 --> 41:13.572
- And we're off.
Great show, ladies.

41:13.605 --> 41:14.640
- Thank you, Cole.

41:17.709 --> 41:19.277
- Another day, another show.

41:19.310 --> 41:21.179
- Is the mic off?

41:21.212 --> 41:22.714
- You guys want sodas?

41:24.816 --> 41:25.817
- No, thank you.

41:28.787 --> 41:30.088
- Okay.
- It's been really bugging me.

41:30.121 --> 41:32.257
You caught them
red-handed?

41:32.290 --> 41:33.992
Well, what did they say
when you busted them?

41:35.594 --> 41:37.028
- Okay.

41:39.798 --> 41:41.867
- I didn't.
- What?

41:41.900 --> 41:44.670
Why don't you
just confront them?

41:44.703 --> 41:47.673
- What are you doing, Olivia?

41:47.706 --> 41:49.274
- They'd never understand,

41:49.307 --> 41:50.676
and they're not
taking things anymore.

41:50.709 --> 41:52.544
They were just--

41:52.578 --> 41:54.045
- Honestly, Jen, I know
you don't want to hear this,

41:54.079 --> 41:57.783
but I think they belong back
with social services.

41:57.816 --> 41:59.985
I just get a really bad
feeling about all this.

42:04.990 --> 42:06.658
- What are you doing?

42:06.692 --> 42:08.560
- Shutting her up.

42:08.594 --> 42:10.596
- Shouldn't we tell Mom?

42:10.629 --> 42:11.863
- Mom's not here.

42:14.032 --> 42:15.867
- Jen?

42:15.901 --> 42:16.868
- What is going on?

42:16.902 --> 42:18.303
- I keep feeling like

42:18.336 --> 42:20.639
Mom's going to be
abandoned by us,

42:20.672 --> 42:21.940
and I can't
deal with it knowing

42:21.973 --> 42:23.575
that we're living
in a nice house,

42:23.609 --> 42:25.944
and she's in the hospital.

42:25.977 --> 42:29.681
- Your mother does not
feel abandoned by you.

42:29.715 --> 42:31.817
She's happy that you guys
are taken care of.

42:31.850 --> 42:33.251
She wants you to have fun.

42:33.284 --> 42:36.688
- I feel bad for her.

42:36.722 --> 42:39.124
It's like we don't know
what's right anymore.

42:39.157 --> 42:41.760
- Olivia, you deserve
to be happy.

42:41.793 --> 42:44.029
- I guess.
But--

42:47.332 --> 42:49.968
Hey.

42:50.001 --> 42:52.070
what about
beach day therapy?

42:55.774 --> 42:59.377
- I think that sounds
like a great idea.

42:59.410 --> 43:02.914
- I think we could all use one
and Gail too.

43:06.084 --> 43:07.786
- I wouldn't
miss it.

43:23.869 --> 43:26.705
[waves crashing]

43:37.348 --> 43:38.917
- I'm gonna give you our stuff,

43:38.950 --> 43:40.752
and I'm gonna get
a quick run in.

43:40.786 --> 43:42.654
Okay?
- Yeah. Sounds good.

43:42.688 --> 43:44.956
- You all right with the girls?
- Oh, yeah. Have a good one.

43:58.436 --> 44:00.739
- Olivia,
why are we over here?

44:00.772 --> 44:02.373
You're leaving me out again,
aren't you?

44:07.445 --> 44:09.247
- Hey, guys.
- it's cool, isn't it?

44:09.280 --> 44:11.883
It's kind of like
our own private beach.

44:11.917 --> 44:13.151
- Yeah.

44:14.853 --> 44:16.187
- Hey, what if we have

44:16.221 --> 44:18.389
our own private spa day?

44:18.423 --> 44:22.160
Come to Private Rock Spa.

44:22.193 --> 44:25.463
- Okay.
I'll have the regular, please.

44:25.496 --> 44:26.998
- Exactly what we thought.

44:27.032 --> 44:30.101
One full-body deluxe,
your regular.

44:38.276 --> 44:40.812
We are here to please.

44:40.846 --> 44:42.380
- I see that.

44:42.413 --> 44:45.817
[laughter]

44:45.851 --> 44:47.986
- Now we just need
some sun protection.

44:51.990 --> 44:53.959
Your treatment bed awaits.

44:53.992 --> 44:56.294
- Ah, thank you.

44:58.029 --> 45:00.832
Ah.

45:00.866 --> 45:02.267
[sighs]

45:02.300 --> 45:04.135
Ah.

45:04.169 --> 45:05.771
[laughs]

45:05.804 --> 45:08.206
[sighs]
Ah, that feels fabulous.

45:09.775 --> 45:12.510
[plaintive music]

45:12.543 --> 45:19.450
*

45:19.484 --> 45:22.854
- Now, if I could just
get some help from Quinn.

45:22.888 --> 45:25.223
Like I said, Gail's gonna need
some sunblock.

45:31.296 --> 45:33.398
Sorry.
We don't want wrinkles.

45:39.905 --> 45:43.041
[ominous music]

45:43.074 --> 45:49.948
*

45:54.485 --> 45:57.288
[waves crashing]

46:00.225 --> 46:01.860
- Hey, Olivia,

46:01.893 --> 46:03.194
I think we better pack it in.

46:03.228 --> 46:05.230
The tide's coming in
pretty fast.

46:09.267 --> 46:11.102
Olivia.

46:11.136 --> 46:12.503
Hey!

46:12.537 --> 46:13.538
Earth to Olivia.

46:16.574 --> 46:17.542
Hey!

46:22.213 --> 46:23.448
Olivia!

46:25.016 --> 46:26.284
Come on.
This isn't fun anymore.

46:29.955 --> 46:31.489
- It kind of is.

46:38.363 --> 46:41.332
- Olivia, help
dig me out, please.

46:41.366 --> 46:42.500
Olivia,
what are you doing?

46:42.533 --> 46:44.602
This isn't funny.

46:44.635 --> 46:46.237
- No.

46:46.271 --> 46:48.339
It's not fun, is it?

46:48.373 --> 46:49.975
Neither is
putting crazy ideas

46:50.008 --> 46:52.410
in Jen's head,
like sending us back.

46:52.443 --> 46:55.313
[waves crashing]

46:55.346 --> 46:56.848
- Olivia, I--

46:56.882 --> 46:58.283
Come on.
I didn't mean that.

46:58.316 --> 47:00.185
Help me out, please?

47:00.218 --> 47:02.253
I need your help
to get out of here, please.

47:02.287 --> 47:03.154
Olivia.

47:05.957 --> 47:07.258
Olivia.

47:07.292 --> 47:08.493
[grunts]

47:08.526 --> 47:10.862
[waves crash]

47:10.896 --> 47:12.964
[grunting]

47:12.998 --> 47:14.332
Quinn!

47:14.365 --> 47:15.867
- [laughs]

47:15.901 --> 47:18.636
She can't hear you.

47:18.669 --> 47:20.505
No one can hear you.

47:20.538 --> 47:21.539
- Olivia.

47:21.572 --> 47:23.074
Olivia, please. Come on.

47:24.342 --> 47:26.611
Help!

47:26.644 --> 47:29.080
Please, Olivia--

47:29.114 --> 47:31.016
Stop.

47:31.049 --> 47:32.417
[coughs]
Help me--

47:32.450 --> 47:33.618
- [laughs]

47:33.651 --> 47:35.620
- Help!

47:35.653 --> 47:38.123
Quinn!

47:38.156 --> 47:39.624
Jen!

47:39.657 --> 47:42.327
[grunts]
Help!

47:42.360 --> 47:45.563
[waves crash]

47:45.596 --> 47:47.265
Help me!

47:47.298 --> 47:49.567
[waves crash]

47:49.600 --> 47:52.470
Please, help!

47:52.503 --> 47:54.072
[waves crash]

47:54.105 --> 47:55.573
[coughs]

47:55.606 --> 47:58.043
[waves crash]

47:58.076 --> 47:59.410
Help me!

47:59.444 --> 48:02.247
[dramatic music]

48:02.280 --> 48:07.352
*

48:07.385 --> 48:10.188
[waves crash]

48:27.572 --> 48:28.940
- Where's Gail?

48:39.717 --> 48:42.620
[plaintive music]

48:42.653 --> 48:47.358
*

48:47.392 --> 48:50.428
- Hey, are you guys
having fun?

48:50.461 --> 48:52.263
- Yeah.

48:54.565 --> 48:57.368
- Where's Gail?

48:57.402 --> 48:59.137
- I don't know.

48:59.170 --> 49:00.271
- Huh.

49:03.474 --> 49:06.577
Well, we should probably
head back soon.

49:06.611 --> 49:08.613
What do you think?
- Hey, it's Gail.

49:08.646 --> 49:09.981
You know what to do.

49:12.250 --> 49:14.119
- That's not really like her.

49:14.152 --> 49:15.420
Why don't we head
back to the car?

49:15.453 --> 49:17.355
Maybe she's waiting
for us there.

49:17.388 --> 49:18.456
- Okay.

49:20.291 --> 49:21.359
- Quinn!

49:21.392 --> 49:22.360
Come on.

49:22.393 --> 49:23.594
Let's go!

49:42.580 --> 49:45.383
[phone ringing quietly]

49:48.219 --> 49:51.022
[phone continues ringing
quietly]

49:52.390 --> 49:55.393
[phone ringing]

49:55.426 --> 49:56.794
- Hey, it's Gail.

49:56.827 --> 49:58.329
You know what to do.
[line beeps]

50:02.567 --> 50:06.071
- I couldn't have been running
longer than 30 minutes.

50:06.104 --> 50:08.306
- You girls didn't see anything,
see anyone else?

50:08.339 --> 50:10.241
- No.
Nothing.

50:10.275 --> 50:11.742
- You know, this beach is
usually pretty dead

50:11.776 --> 50:14.412
during the week, like today.

50:14.445 --> 50:17.115
- One of the girls pointed
towards Pirate Rock,

50:17.148 --> 50:19.184
said she saw her
walk there.

50:19.217 --> 50:22.253
- Gail's not a good swimmer.

50:22.287 --> 50:23.788
I think you need
to check the water.

50:26.657 --> 50:29.494
Please, please,
go check the water, please.

50:29.527 --> 50:31.762
- Requesting Coast Guard assist,
Pirate Rock. Over.

50:33.498 --> 50:36.367
- [sobbing]

50:42.773 --> 50:45.543
- All right.
The coastline is clear.

50:48.513 --> 50:49.680
- Sit tight.

50:52.550 --> 50:55.520
Check on the south beach too.

50:55.553 --> 50:57.122
- Sheriff, hurry!

50:57.155 --> 50:58.823
There's something
out by the water.

50:58.856 --> 51:00.591
- All right.
Hey, guys, we got her.

51:00.625 --> 51:01.659
- Oh, no, no.

51:01.692 --> 51:03.594
- Oh, Gail--
- No, no--

51:03.628 --> 51:05.096
[sobbing]

51:05.130 --> 51:08.233
- Everybody, down here now.

51:08.266 --> 51:10.268
All right.
Secure the perimeter.

51:10.301 --> 51:12.603
- Oh, no, no.
[sobbing]

51:12.637 --> 51:18.176
[indistinct police radio
chatter]

51:18.209 --> 51:21.078
[waves crashing]

51:50.441 --> 51:51.742
- I think that's it.

51:54.412 --> 51:55.613
- Thank you.

51:58.316 --> 52:02.253
I just can't believe she's gone.

52:02.287 --> 52:05.190
I keep thinking that she's just
gonna walk in the door

52:05.223 --> 52:07.792
any minute
all happy and cheery.

52:11.262 --> 52:13.498
Just--

52:13.531 --> 52:15.866
I can't imagine
what her family's going through.

52:17.535 --> 52:19.204
- Hey.

52:20.871 --> 52:23.140
This is a rough time
for you too.

52:27.212 --> 52:29.280
I'll just put this
in the garage.

52:31.416 --> 52:32.650
- Thank you.

52:41.692 --> 52:43.528
- I bet it's rough
on the girls too.

52:56.341 --> 52:59.810
First the trauma with
their mother, and now this.

53:05.950 --> 53:07.685
- She wanted to send us away,
Quinn.

53:07.718 --> 53:09.254
Didn't you hear her?

53:09.287 --> 53:10.421
- It's wrong.
This is all wrong.

53:10.455 --> 53:12.490
- What's wrong is Jen's will.

53:12.523 --> 53:13.958
That's wrong, Quinn.

53:13.991 --> 53:16.561
We need to go
see Mom right away.

53:16.594 --> 53:18.663
I need you with me
on this, Sissy.

53:18.696 --> 53:21.532
We need to be together.

53:21.566 --> 53:24.435
- You killed someone, Olivia.

53:24.469 --> 53:26.003
- My commitment is to you

53:26.036 --> 53:27.972
and Mom, Quinn.

53:28.005 --> 53:29.874
I'm committed
to saving our family.

53:29.907 --> 53:31.208
Are you?

53:38.883 --> 53:40.685
See, we're like this bee.

53:40.718 --> 53:43.488
One little bee
can't hurt me,

53:43.521 --> 53:44.922
but a swarm--

53:44.955 --> 53:47.792
[faint buzzing]

53:49.460 --> 53:52.330
[loud buzzing]

53:54.765 --> 53:57.702
[ominous music]

53:57.735 --> 54:02.973
*

54:05.576 --> 54:08.513
[delicate music]

54:08.546 --> 54:15.420
*

55:04.435 --> 55:05.570
- Girls?

55:05.603 --> 55:06.971
[knock at door]

55:17.782 --> 55:18.816
Girls?

55:27.758 --> 55:30.761
I think we probably
could've talked about this.

55:30.795 --> 55:32.563
If you guys feel like this is

55:32.597 --> 55:33.998
gonna make
the adjustment easier,

55:34.031 --> 55:37.435
then we can stick to one room
for right now.

55:37.468 --> 55:39.637
But we're gonna
talk about things, okay?

55:39.670 --> 55:41.338
No subject
is off-limits.

55:43.708 --> 55:45.810
- We want to see our mom.

55:45.843 --> 55:47.612
With everything that's
going on, Aunt Jen,

55:47.645 --> 55:48.746
we need to see her.

55:51.982 --> 55:53.818
- I will talk to Dr. Martine.

55:55.486 --> 55:56.487
Okay?

56:19.477 --> 56:21.712
- Here.
Let me show you our selfies.

56:21.746 --> 56:23.147
- Oh, yes.

56:23.180 --> 56:24.482
Show me everything.

56:36.727 --> 56:39.697
This shot would be
so much better if I was in it.

56:39.730 --> 56:40.931
Don't you think?

56:40.965 --> 56:42.533
- Yeah.

56:42.567 --> 56:43.901
Quinn and I
aren't in it either.

56:45.603 --> 56:47.872
- Although
this looks promising.

56:57.848 --> 57:00.651
I have
the game-changing word.

57:00.685 --> 57:02.453
- I know.

57:03.888 --> 57:06.056
- [laughs]

57:09.560 --> 57:10.995
It's a new game.

57:18.603 --> 57:19.870
Get it?

57:19.904 --> 57:21.639
- No.

57:21.672 --> 57:23.007
- Quinn, honey,
just watch Olivia.

57:23.040 --> 57:24.642
She knows what to do.

57:34.685 --> 57:36.487
- What was
all that about?

57:38.122 --> 57:39.757
- It means, dummy,

57:39.790 --> 57:41.992
that we need to
get adopted by Jen.

57:42.026 --> 57:43.861
- Adopted?

57:43.894 --> 57:45.796
But why do we want that?

57:45.830 --> 57:47.131
- So that we inherit everything.

57:47.164 --> 57:50.200
Get it?
You, me, and Mom.

57:52.069 --> 57:53.470
- Take care.
- Thank you.

57:58.676 --> 58:00.244
Okay.

58:00.277 --> 58:02.112
Well, did you guys
have a nice visit with your mom?

58:04.849 --> 58:06.884
- Hey, Jen?
- Yeah?

58:06.917 --> 58:08.786
- Thank you so much
for helping us.

58:08.819 --> 58:11.055
Quinn and I
really appreciate it.

58:11.088 --> 58:13.290
- Of course.

58:13.323 --> 58:16.226
You know you girls
mean the world to me.

58:16.260 --> 58:17.862
Come on.
Let's go home.

58:25.770 --> 58:28.973
- Aunt Jen, can we talk to you?

58:29.006 --> 58:30.808
It's been real hard,
Aunt Jen.

58:30.841 --> 58:33.077
CPS came to the house
six times--

58:33.110 --> 58:36.080
- Seven times, Quinn.

58:36.113 --> 58:37.715
Each time we would move,

58:37.748 --> 58:39.550
but it would just
happen again.

58:41.351 --> 58:45.322
- I am so glad you girls
are finally opening up to me.

58:45.355 --> 58:49.994
Look, I need you girls
to know your mom isn't bad.

58:50.027 --> 58:51.629
Okay?
She's sick.

58:51.662 --> 58:53.197
And she needs help.

58:56.200 --> 58:58.769
- We're afraid of her, Jen.

58:58.803 --> 59:00.871
Look, Mom's scary
when she gets crazy.

59:00.905 --> 59:03.240
Did you see our house?

59:03.273 --> 59:04.875
- I did.
Yeah.

59:04.909 --> 59:06.176
- You say that we're safe,

59:06.210 --> 59:08.245
but what happens
when she gets out?

59:08.278 --> 59:11.015
Are we supposed
to go back with her?

59:11.048 --> 59:14.084
- Are you really afraid?

59:14.118 --> 59:15.185
- [sniffles] Yeah.
We both are.

59:17.387 --> 59:19.023
We just can't go back to her.

59:21.325 --> 59:24.829
- What do you guys, um...

59:24.862 --> 59:26.964
what do you guys think
about coming here

59:26.997 --> 59:29.600
and living with me?

59:29.634 --> 59:31.769
- You can do that?

59:31.802 --> 59:33.237
- We can talk to your mom

59:33.270 --> 59:35.840
and try to
make her understand

59:35.873 --> 59:38.242
that we want to help her.

59:38.275 --> 59:39.977
You know, due to her
long-term treatment,

59:40.010 --> 59:41.912
it could be that a guardianship

59:41.946 --> 59:45.750
or even an adoption
could be an option.

59:47.184 --> 59:49.286
- An adoption?

59:49.319 --> 59:50.755
- Yeah, I mean,

59:50.788 --> 59:52.022
you guys and your mom
would have to agree,

59:52.056 --> 59:54.759
but yeah.

59:54.792 --> 59:56.961
- So well, what do you--
what do you mean?

59:56.994 --> 59:59.129
Like, what would that--
what would happen?

59:59.163 --> 01:00:04.669
- We would become
a new kind of family.

01:00:04.702 --> 01:00:07.772
We would have an open
and honest relationship,

01:00:07.805 --> 01:00:10.941
and you would start school
in the fall.

01:00:13.243 --> 01:00:15.112
For the first time
in a long time,

01:00:15.145 --> 01:00:18.148
you guys would have a place
to call home.

01:00:18.182 --> 01:00:19.917
- [sniffles]

01:00:19.950 --> 01:00:22.619
- What's mine would be yours.

01:00:28.058 --> 01:00:31.261
I mean, the attorney said
considering Cassie's history,

01:00:31.295 --> 01:00:34.364
I have a real chance.

01:00:34.398 --> 01:00:36.901
The girls even told me
that they're afraid of her.

01:00:36.934 --> 01:00:39.904
They don't want
to go back to her.

01:00:39.937 --> 01:00:42.239
The minute that a children's
court hears that,

01:00:42.272 --> 01:00:44.108
they're gonna want to
push this through quickly.

01:00:46.143 --> 01:00:47.277
What?

01:00:49.847 --> 01:00:52.249
Baby, come on.
What are you thinking?

01:00:52.282 --> 01:00:55.119
- I don't know, Jen.

01:00:55.152 --> 01:00:58.155
It just seems that

01:00:58.188 --> 01:01:00.958
they're too close. You know?

01:01:00.991 --> 01:01:02.192
It's like they need--
- They're--

01:01:02.226 --> 01:01:03.761
- It's like they need

01:01:03.794 --> 01:01:07.698
to be together to survive,
to breathe.

01:01:07.732 --> 01:01:12.169
Those two girls are never apart.

01:01:12.202 --> 01:01:13.971
And I know
you're the doctor here,

01:01:14.004 --> 01:01:17.842
but I don't think that's healthy
for them or for you.

01:01:17.875 --> 01:01:19.176
- [sighs]

01:01:19.209 --> 01:01:21.245
I worry about it too,
you know? And--

01:01:24.081 --> 01:01:26.350
- Look, I'm just gonna
go out and say it,

01:01:26.383 --> 01:01:29.019
because I've been thinking
about this, and I'm--

01:01:29.053 --> 01:01:30.287
- What?

01:01:30.320 --> 01:01:33.924
- I'm wondering if adopting them

01:01:33.958 --> 01:01:36.093
is such a great idea.

01:01:36.126 --> 01:01:38.462
- [sighs]

01:01:38.495 --> 01:01:41.265
I know--I know
that they're troubled.

01:01:41.298 --> 01:01:43.400
Okay?

01:01:43.433 --> 01:01:44.401
But they've been better.

01:01:46.070 --> 01:01:48.272
Kevin, I mean,

01:01:48.305 --> 01:01:50.775
those girls are my family.

01:01:50.808 --> 01:01:52.943
- I know.

01:01:52.977 --> 01:01:55.846
But I'm pretty sure they were
behind the glass in the lounger.

01:01:55.880 --> 01:01:59.216
I know they
stole from you.

01:01:59.249 --> 01:02:01.051
You know that
they put acid

01:02:01.085 --> 01:02:02.286
in your lotion,
for God's sakes.

01:02:02.319 --> 01:02:03.520
What's next?

01:02:03.553 --> 01:02:04.889
- I know
they've been acting out.

01:02:04.922 --> 01:02:06.891
Okay?

01:02:06.924 --> 01:02:09.493
But they're getting better.
They're happy, even.

01:02:09.526 --> 01:02:13.163
I mean, I have a real shot at
putting my family back together.

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:17.334
- I know that's
really important to you.

01:02:17.367 --> 01:02:19.369
- It is.

01:02:19.403 --> 01:02:23.874
- But something about them
doesn't feel right.

01:02:23.908 --> 01:02:26.210
And...

01:02:26.243 --> 01:02:28.846
I think you should
reconsider the option

01:02:28.879 --> 01:02:30.414
until everything's
ironed out.

01:02:41.125 --> 01:02:42.459
- Girls, I'm gonna head
to the store.

01:02:42.492 --> 01:02:44.461
Do you need anything else?

01:02:44.494 --> 01:02:46.063
- Don't forget pasta.
- Yeah.

01:02:46.096 --> 01:02:47.531
We're making dinner
tonight.

01:02:47.564 --> 01:02:49.333
- Oh.

01:02:49.366 --> 01:02:51.568
- Is Kevin still coming over?

01:02:51.601 --> 01:02:53.237
- Yes. He's very excited.

01:03:01.111 --> 01:03:02.947
See you guys later.

01:03:22.366 --> 01:03:23.968
- Come on, Quinn.

01:03:24.001 --> 01:03:26.003
- Do we even know
where we're going?

01:03:26.036 --> 01:03:28.138
- Mom says this is
the best place to go.

01:03:28.172 --> 01:03:30.107
- Go for what?

01:03:50.995 --> 01:03:52.262
[dog barks]

01:03:58.168 --> 01:03:59.169
- Hello.

01:03:59.203 --> 01:04:00.470
- Good morning.

01:04:02.439 --> 01:04:04.174
- Don't let
your sister eat those.

01:04:09.113 --> 01:04:11.481
Those are death caps.
They're poisonous.

01:04:28.465 --> 01:04:29.599
- What did she want?

01:04:31.035 --> 01:04:32.202
- Nothing.

01:04:35.505 --> 01:04:38.475
[water bubbling]

01:04:38.508 --> 01:04:41.478
[knife chopping]

01:04:41.511 --> 01:04:44.448
[suspenseful music]

01:04:44.481 --> 01:04:51.355
*

01:04:53.423 --> 01:04:54.992
- Just keep
slicing your carrots

01:04:55.025 --> 01:04:56.526
and don't do
anything stupid.

01:05:05.970 --> 01:05:07.404
- Stop it.

01:05:13.410 --> 01:05:15.079
- What's wrong?

01:05:17.714 --> 01:05:19.583
You don't think
I'd hurt you, do you?

01:05:20.750 --> 01:05:23.553
[timer buzzing, dings]

01:05:47.344 --> 01:05:51.448
Good evening,
Ms. Burgess and Kevin.

01:05:51.481 --> 01:05:52.616
- Mmm.

01:05:52.649 --> 01:05:54.718
- [laughs]
both: Oh.

01:05:54.751 --> 01:05:57.988
- Kevin gets the big plate,
because he's a big man.

01:05:59.723 --> 01:06:02.326
- Wow.
This is a big helping.

01:06:02.359 --> 01:06:04.461
- Girls,
this was very sweet.

01:06:04.494 --> 01:06:07.331
Thank you.
It looks really good.

01:06:07.364 --> 01:06:09.133
- Just think.

01:06:09.166 --> 01:06:11.101
Soon we'll be a family...

01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:15.339
all of us.

01:06:15.372 --> 01:06:16.606
You too, Kevin.

01:06:21.178 --> 01:06:23.780
- Okay.
Cheers.

01:06:23.813 --> 01:06:24.981
- Bon apptit.

01:06:33.190 --> 01:06:37.427
Mmm-mmm-mmm.

01:06:37.461 --> 01:06:38.695
- You know,

01:06:38.728 --> 01:06:42.266
I didn't get
very many mushrooms.

01:06:42.299 --> 01:06:43.200
- You want some of mine?

01:06:43.233 --> 01:06:44.268
- Yeah.

01:06:44.301 --> 01:06:46.136
That would be great.

01:06:46.170 --> 01:06:48.038
Thank you.
- Have plenty.

01:06:48.072 --> 01:06:50.207
- Thank you.
Thank you.

01:06:50.240 --> 01:06:51.475
Q?

01:06:58.148 --> 01:06:59.183
- Quinn,

01:06:59.216 --> 01:07:00.650
On't-day eat-ay.

01:07:02.419 --> 01:07:04.688
On't-day ea-tay
ha-tay.

01:07:04.721 --> 01:07:05.589
Quinn.

01:07:07.391 --> 01:07:09.126
Quinn.

01:07:09.159 --> 01:07:10.660
Quinn, can I talk to you
for a second

01:07:10.694 --> 01:07:11.628
in the other room?

01:07:13.730 --> 01:07:14.698
- Mm-hmm.

01:07:21.105 --> 01:07:22.772
- Why did you do that?

01:07:22.806 --> 01:07:24.441
- What do you--

01:07:24.474 --> 01:07:25.742
- Quinn, you need
to go to the bathroom.

01:07:25.775 --> 01:07:26.810
You need to make the mushrooms
come up now.

01:07:26.843 --> 01:07:28.578
Please, just do it.

01:07:28.612 --> 01:07:30.614
- Why, Olivia?

01:07:30.647 --> 01:07:32.082
You wanted to kill just Kevin?

01:07:32.116 --> 01:07:33.350
Is that it?

01:07:37.787 --> 01:07:40.857
- So you knew the mushrooms
were poisonous.

01:07:40.890 --> 01:07:43.327
You switched them.
Quinn.

01:07:43.360 --> 01:07:48.098
Look, you think what you
did was right, but it's not.

01:07:48.132 --> 01:07:50.600
- And what you did
to Gail was right?

01:07:53.437 --> 01:07:54.871
- He is putting the idea

01:07:54.904 --> 01:07:57.574
of stopping the adoption
into Jen's head.

01:07:57.607 --> 01:07:59.776
He's going to mess this up.

01:07:59.809 --> 01:08:03.247
I am looking out
for Mom and us.

01:08:07.251 --> 01:08:08.418
Quinn.

01:08:53.729 --> 01:08:57.167
- So happy to see you
up close.

01:08:57.201 --> 01:09:00.837
It's been so long.

01:09:00.870 --> 01:09:03.139
I missed you so much, Sis.

01:09:21.457 --> 01:09:23.926
Thank you for seeing me.

01:09:23.960 --> 01:09:26.395
I'm so happy you've been
so open to getting better

01:09:26.430 --> 01:09:30.234
and just making
your life easier.

01:09:30.267 --> 01:09:32.368
- Yeah.
Well, I tend to mess things up.

01:09:32.402 --> 01:09:33.803
Don't I?

01:09:33.837 --> 01:09:36.305
- Getting better--
that's all that matters.

01:09:42.946 --> 01:09:45.682
I want to talk to you
about something,

01:09:45.715 --> 01:09:48.518
something that's gonna
help you and the girls.

01:09:48.551 --> 01:09:50.319
- Well, I'm no mother
of the year,

01:09:50.354 --> 01:09:53.857
but I certainly want
what's best for my girls.

01:09:53.890 --> 01:09:56.660
Lately, it's dawned on me

01:09:56.693 --> 01:09:59.263
[scoffs]

01:09:59.296 --> 01:10:00.897
I'm not doing
such a bang-up job.

01:10:02.266 --> 01:10:03.367
- [chuckles]

01:10:05.702 --> 01:10:08.472
This is gonna be
a sensitive subject,

01:10:08.505 --> 01:10:10.006
and I want you
to just hear me out.

01:10:10.039 --> 01:10:11.775
Okay?

01:10:11.808 --> 01:10:13.443
I've gone back and forth

01:10:13.477 --> 01:10:15.612
in my mind so many times,

01:10:15.645 --> 01:10:18.348
and I've weighed--and
I've weighed all the options

01:10:18.382 --> 01:10:20.650
about what would be
the best thing

01:10:20.684 --> 01:10:22.919
for you, for the girls,

01:10:22.952 --> 01:10:26.656
and they're doing so well
with me, Cassie.

01:10:29.359 --> 01:10:32.662
- They do seem better.

01:10:32.696 --> 01:10:34.230
- They really are.

01:10:36.333 --> 01:10:37.901
I'm wondering how you
would feel about

01:10:37.934 --> 01:10:40.304
if they stayed
with me

01:10:40.337 --> 01:10:42.539
permanently.

01:10:42.572 --> 01:10:45.675
I think it would be
a really good thing for you.

01:10:45.709 --> 01:10:47.844
I think you could focus
on your healing.

01:10:47.877 --> 01:10:50.614
You could stop
worrying about them.

01:10:50.647 --> 01:10:54.484
I actually spoke to the girls
about it already, and...

01:10:54.518 --> 01:10:57.421
you know,
they're such sweet girls.

01:10:57.454 --> 01:10:59.956
They're really worried
about your feelings,

01:10:59.989 --> 01:11:05.028
how you're gonna feel
about all of this.

01:11:05.061 --> 01:11:06.830
But I think
it's what they want too.

01:11:11.901 --> 01:11:17.474
You know, the legal--
the legal course of action,

01:11:17.507 --> 01:11:19.909
I think, would be going through
with an adoption,

01:11:19.943 --> 01:11:22.679
so I could--I could enroll them
in the school by my house,

01:11:22.712 --> 01:11:26.015
and they would start
in the fall,

01:11:26.049 --> 01:11:27.351
and get them ready for college,

01:11:27.384 --> 01:11:28.552
which I would be--

01:11:28.585 --> 01:11:30.754
I would be
so happy to pay for.

01:11:34.123 --> 01:11:38.628
Everything is, um--

01:11:38.662 --> 01:11:40.764
it's outlined here
in these papers.

01:11:40.797 --> 01:11:43.700
Take a look at it,
and see if you--

01:11:43.733 --> 01:11:48.438
- If I even consider this,
I want you to promise me

01:11:48.472 --> 01:11:51.541
I won't lose my girls forever.

01:11:51.575 --> 01:11:54.744
- Cassie, I promise.

01:11:54.778 --> 01:11:57.514
Nothing is forever.

01:11:57.547 --> 01:11:58.982
You are gonna finish
your treatment.

01:11:59.015 --> 01:12:00.484
You are gonna get back
on your feet,

01:12:00.517 --> 01:12:02.652
and with a little time
behind you,

01:12:02.686 --> 01:12:05.054
you're gonna come back to us.
Okay?

01:12:05.088 --> 01:12:08.592
You're gonna live with me
and the girls.

01:12:08.625 --> 01:12:11.495
You are always gonna
be their mother.

01:12:13.663 --> 01:12:15.432
- You got that right.

01:12:20.003 --> 01:12:22.472
But what I can't quit
thinking about is how--

01:12:22.506 --> 01:12:25.975
is how you think
you're saving my girls from me.

01:12:27.477 --> 01:12:29.446
It's how--

01:12:29.479 --> 01:12:32.882
how you think
you're saving my girls from me.

01:12:35.752 --> 01:12:39.055
Jen, Jen, Jen,
Mommy's favorite.

01:12:39.088 --> 01:12:42.058
Little Jenny always
saves the day.

01:12:42.091 --> 01:12:43.026
- Cassie!

01:12:47.063 --> 01:12:48.532
- [sighs]

01:12:48.565 --> 01:12:50.734
Who am I kidding?

01:12:50.767 --> 01:12:54.538
I'm ruining their lives.

01:12:54.571 --> 01:12:57.574
They're better off with you.

01:12:57.607 --> 01:12:59.509
Even I know it.

01:13:04.748 --> 01:13:06.850
I'll sign your papers.

01:13:25.201 --> 01:13:27.070
- Hey.
So...

01:13:27.103 --> 01:13:28.204
we're right
on schedule.

01:13:28.237 --> 01:13:29.673
We're the next
case up.

01:13:29.706 --> 01:13:30.740
- Thanks.

01:13:52.762 --> 01:13:54.864
- The judge is ready
to make a decision.

01:13:54.898 --> 01:13:56.600
He's encouraged by the paperwork
we've provided,

01:13:56.633 --> 01:13:58.735
and even more encouraging
is that Cassie

01:13:58.768 --> 01:14:01.237
willingly signed
the adoption contract

01:14:01.270 --> 01:14:02.706
and refused independent counsel.

01:14:02.739 --> 01:14:04.541
It's a really good sign.

01:14:04.574 --> 01:14:07.143
- I think Cassie's
in agreement that

01:14:07.176 --> 01:14:10.113
this is the right thing
to do for the girls.

01:14:10.146 --> 01:14:11.848
- Ms. Murphy,

01:14:11.881 --> 01:14:13.783
the judge will want to
ask you a few questions.

01:14:15.619 --> 01:14:16.786
- Sure.

01:14:18.588 --> 01:14:20.123
- All rise.

01:14:26.129 --> 01:14:27.764
- Please, be seated.

01:14:31.167 --> 01:14:33.770
Ms. Cassandra Murphy,

01:14:33.803 --> 01:14:36.740
you're the biological mother
of Olivia and Quinn Murphy,

01:14:36.773 --> 01:14:38.207
twins, age 15.

01:14:39.943 --> 01:14:41.678
- Yes, your honor.

01:14:41.711 --> 01:14:43.146
- And Ms. Murphy,

01:14:43.179 --> 01:14:45.515
did you willingly sign
a contract relinquishing

01:14:45.549 --> 01:14:48.251
all parental rights to Olivia
and Quinn Murphy,

01:14:48.284 --> 01:14:50.620
your biological daughters,

01:14:50.654 --> 01:14:52.822
to Ms. Burgess,
your biological sister,

01:14:52.856 --> 01:14:54.958
to fully adopt
the aforementioned daughters?

01:14:54.991 --> 01:14:56.526
- I did.

01:15:00.730 --> 01:15:02.666
- As a family court judge,

01:15:02.699 --> 01:15:05.301
it is very important that
I am convinced a birth mother

01:15:05.334 --> 01:15:06.770
is a willing participant

01:15:06.803 --> 01:15:08.672
when relinquishing
parental rights.

01:15:08.705 --> 01:15:10.206
Do you understand me,
Ms. Murphy?

01:15:15.879 --> 01:15:17.714
- Yeah.

01:15:17.747 --> 01:15:19.215
Yeah, I get it.

01:15:19.248 --> 01:15:21.317
So I can't even put
my kids up for adoption

01:15:21.350 --> 01:15:23.987
without messing that up?

01:15:24.020 --> 01:15:26.590
I'm crazy and completely
unfit to be a mother,

01:15:26.623 --> 01:15:29.258
and she sits here,
perfect.

01:15:29.292 --> 01:15:31.961
She gets everything
she wants.

01:15:31.995 --> 01:15:33.096
Everything!
- Bailiff--

01:15:33.129 --> 01:15:34.330
- Let me go!

01:15:34.363 --> 01:15:35.765
- Take her
out of my courtroom.

01:15:35.799 --> 01:15:37.100
- Yeah, I am
the perfect mother.

01:15:37.133 --> 01:15:39.268
- Bailiff, get her
out of my courtroom now.

01:15:39.302 --> 01:15:41.037
- I want my kids back.

01:15:41.070 --> 01:15:42.672
I want my kids back.
I want them back.

01:15:42.706 --> 01:15:44.974
I want my babies back.
I'm the perfect mother.

01:15:45.008 --> 01:15:46.576
Let me go.

01:15:46.610 --> 01:15:47.944
I want my babies back.

01:15:47.977 --> 01:15:49.278
I'm sorry.

01:15:49.312 --> 01:15:50.313
I'm sorry.

01:15:50.346 --> 01:15:51.715
I'm sorry!

01:16:01.157 --> 01:16:04.060
[plaintive music]

01:16:04.093 --> 01:16:10.967
*

01:16:23.647 --> 01:16:26.349
- So the judge
is granting the adoption.

01:16:26.382 --> 01:16:31.888
See, after the violent outburst,
he felt it better for the girls.

01:16:31.921 --> 01:16:36.726
So congratulations, all of you.

01:16:36.760 --> 01:16:38.662
I hope this is
a healing time for you all.

01:16:38.695 --> 01:16:40.930
I wish you all of the best.

01:16:58.281 --> 01:17:00.116
- I love you, Sis.

01:17:05.922 --> 01:17:07.623
Okay.
Let's go.

01:17:18.768 --> 01:17:23.272
Well, it's official.

01:17:23.306 --> 01:17:26.109
Girls, I just have to tell you
I'm so happy--

01:17:26.142 --> 01:17:29.879
happy for our futures,
and I'm happy for your mom too.

01:17:29.913 --> 01:17:33.282
I just--I love you both so much.

01:17:33.316 --> 01:17:35.819
- We're happy too.

01:17:35.852 --> 01:17:37.687
- We're gonna be a great family.

01:17:55.471 --> 01:17:58.241
I have some good news
for you girls.

01:17:58.274 --> 01:18:03.847
Your mother's doctor approved
her for a free day tomorrow.

01:18:03.880 --> 01:18:08.985
So tomorrow, we are gonna
all go on a picnic together.

01:18:09.018 --> 01:18:11.054
What do you guys
think about that?

01:18:11.087 --> 01:18:12.856
- Cool.

01:18:12.889 --> 01:18:14.357
Where are we going?

01:18:14.390 --> 01:18:16.459
- There is a great little
mountain location

01:18:16.492 --> 01:18:18.227
that your great-grandfather

01:18:18.261 --> 01:18:20.997
used to take your mom and I
to when we were kids.

01:18:21.030 --> 01:18:22.899
It's really beautiful.

01:18:28.404 --> 01:18:30.740
- Olivia, come on.
We have to go and get Mom.

01:18:41.918 --> 01:18:43.186
What are you doing?

01:18:43.219 --> 01:18:45.822
- Stay out of it.

01:18:45.855 --> 01:18:47.056
- You and Mom
are up to something.

01:18:47.090 --> 01:18:48.257
I know it.

01:18:50.159 --> 01:18:51.294
Please, tell me.

01:18:51.327 --> 01:18:52.261
What is it?

01:18:54.197 --> 01:18:56.432
Who's that for?

01:18:56.465 --> 01:19:00.937
- Something for Mom from me.

01:19:00.970 --> 01:19:02.772
- Okay.
Just you.

01:19:05.942 --> 01:19:07.777
What is it?

01:19:07.811 --> 01:19:09.512
- I can't trust you.

01:19:19.288 --> 01:19:22.125
[loud buzzing]

01:19:30.867 --> 01:19:32.035
- Okay.

01:19:32.068 --> 01:19:33.169
You guys, we're gonna be late.

01:19:33.202 --> 01:19:34.203
Where's your sister?

01:19:35.604 --> 01:19:36.539
Quinn?

01:19:53.389 --> 01:19:56.325
[portentous music]

01:19:56.359 --> 01:20:03.199
*

01:20:33.129 --> 01:20:34.964
[eagle cries]

01:20:39.602 --> 01:20:42.505
[mysterious music]

01:20:42.538 --> 01:20:48.011
*

01:20:48.044 --> 01:20:49.979
- Girls, your grandfather
used to take

01:20:50.013 --> 01:20:52.181
your mom and I
up this same road,

01:20:52.215 --> 01:20:54.483
except for we would drive in
the back of his pick-up truck.

01:20:54.517 --> 01:20:56.219
Mom used to come with us
too sometimes.

01:20:56.252 --> 01:20:57.286
Right?

01:20:57.320 --> 01:20:58.888
- Maybe.

01:20:58.922 --> 01:21:00.256
She had better things to do,

01:21:00.289 --> 01:21:03.559
usually with someone
named Rocko or Bud.

01:21:03.592 --> 01:21:05.294
- She wasn't all that bad.

01:21:05.328 --> 01:21:06.562
- Easy for you to say.

01:21:06.595 --> 01:21:08.064
She was a lot nicer to you.

01:21:08.097 --> 01:21:09.032
- Mom, I got you something.

01:21:09.065 --> 01:21:10.033
- Can't you wait?

01:21:12.001 --> 01:21:13.369
- You know, we don't
have to talk about this.

01:21:13.402 --> 01:21:15.204
We can--we could talk about
something else.

01:21:15.238 --> 01:21:17.306
- No, no.
It's okay.

01:21:17.340 --> 01:21:18.607
I can talk about it all.

01:21:18.641 --> 01:21:20.476
I'm telling you, Jen.

01:21:20.509 --> 01:21:23.146
I can see clearly now.

01:21:23.179 --> 01:21:25.982
It dawned on me
just the other day

01:21:26.015 --> 01:21:29.318
how much Mom came between us.

01:21:29.352 --> 01:21:31.054
- She was troubled.
She was unstable.

01:21:31.087 --> 01:21:32.621
- Unstable?

01:21:32.655 --> 01:21:34.223
[laughs]

01:21:34.257 --> 01:21:37.293
Mom was crazy
as a jaybird.

01:21:37.326 --> 01:21:39.328
Come on.
You can admit it.

01:21:39.362 --> 01:21:45.001
Jen Burgess, great radio shrink,
had a crazy mom.

01:21:45.034 --> 01:21:46.435
[laughs]
- You know what, girls?

01:21:46.469 --> 01:21:48.071
It's a long way
to the top of the mountain.

01:21:48.104 --> 01:21:49.538
Does anyone need
a bathroom break?

01:21:49.572 --> 01:21:50.639
- You girls can hold it.
Right?

01:21:50.673 --> 01:21:52.008
- We're fine.

01:21:52.041 --> 01:21:53.576
Do you want to open
your gift now?

01:21:53.609 --> 01:21:56.579
- No, hon.
Let's save it.

01:21:56.612 --> 01:21:57.680
Let's just
enjoy the view.

01:22:18.734 --> 01:22:20.736
Are you okay, sweetie?

01:22:20.769 --> 01:22:22.171
- Yeah.

01:22:22.205 --> 01:22:23.172
- [laughs]

01:22:23.206 --> 01:22:24.707
- Cass--

01:22:24.740 --> 01:22:26.409
- What's it like, Jen,

01:22:26.442 --> 01:22:28.711
to get everything
you want?

01:22:28.744 --> 01:22:30.679
Because you do, right?

01:22:30.713 --> 01:22:33.516
[laughs]
You got me locked up.

01:22:33.549 --> 01:22:36.185
You adopted
both of my girls.

01:22:36.219 --> 01:22:37.653
I'm just curious what's next.

01:22:37.686 --> 01:22:39.222
- All right.
- I know what you think is next.

01:22:39.255 --> 01:22:41.290
- Okay, Cassie--

01:22:41.324 --> 01:22:43.993
- You think you're in control
of everything, don't you?

01:22:44.027 --> 01:22:45.394
- Okay. We're done.
You know what?

01:22:45.428 --> 01:22:46.762
I think we should just go back.

01:22:46.795 --> 01:22:48.731
- [laughs]
No, no.

01:22:48.764 --> 01:22:52.501
Seriously,
this is therapeutic for me.

01:22:52.535 --> 01:22:55.371
In fact, I think I'm about
to feel so much better.

01:22:55.404 --> 01:22:56.572
- You know what?
We're gonna go--

01:22:56.605 --> 01:22:59.342
- Olivia, let me
have that present.

01:22:59.375 --> 01:23:01.144
- We are just gonna
do this another day. Okay?

01:23:01.177 --> 01:23:03.512
- Thanks, sweetie.
No, no, no, no.

01:23:03.546 --> 01:23:04.580
This is the perfect gift...

01:23:04.613 --> 01:23:06.449
- What is that?
- [laughing]

01:23:06.482 --> 01:23:10.053
- For the perfect family.

01:23:10.086 --> 01:23:11.387
- Olivia, what is that?

01:23:11.420 --> 01:23:13.589
- You're gonna love it.
[laughter]

01:23:13.622 --> 01:23:15.758
- What are you doing?

01:23:15.791 --> 01:23:18.361
- [laughing]
- Cassie, what are you doing?

01:23:18.394 --> 01:23:21.197
- [laughing]

01:23:21.230 --> 01:23:23.766
- [gasps] Surprise.

01:23:23.799 --> 01:23:25.268
[loud buzzing]
- Cassie!

01:23:25.301 --> 01:23:27.570
[both screaming]

01:23:27.603 --> 01:23:29.305
- No!
Cassie!

01:23:29.338 --> 01:23:31.207
[tires squeal]

01:23:31.240 --> 01:23:33.242
- Cassie!
- [laughter]

01:23:33.276 --> 01:23:34.810
[laughter]

01:23:34.843 --> 01:23:36.612
- [yelping]

01:23:36.645 --> 01:23:39.415
[tires squealing]

01:23:39.448 --> 01:23:41.717
- [laughs]

01:23:41.750 --> 01:23:43.086
Get it.
Whoo!

01:23:43.119 --> 01:23:45.188
[loud buzzing]

01:23:45.221 --> 01:23:47.090
Oh, they got you.

01:23:47.123 --> 01:23:49.325
They got you, didn't they?
[laughs]

01:23:49.358 --> 01:23:51.194
Oh, are they in your hair?

01:23:51.227 --> 01:23:53.696
Oh, yeah.
Oh, oh--

01:23:53.729 --> 01:23:56.232
- Cassie, you know I'll die--

01:23:56.265 --> 01:23:57.600
- What?

01:23:57.633 --> 01:23:59.602
She deserves it,
Quinn.

01:23:59.635 --> 01:24:00.703
She left us alone.

01:24:00.736 --> 01:24:02.838
She's ashamed of her own family.

01:24:02.871 --> 01:24:07.576
Well, you're not looking
so pretty now, are you, Sissy?

01:24:07.610 --> 01:24:10.479
No. You're looking
kind of heinous.

01:24:10.513 --> 01:24:12.648
